# Git for deployment (canonical)

This repository **uses Git**. **Default production deploy** is **`git add`** → **`git commit`** → **`git push`** to the branch Railway watches (usually **`main`**). That push triggers Railway when the service is connected to GitHub.

## Assistant rules

1. On **deploy**, **redeploy**, **ship**, **commit**, **save**, **commit and deploy**, or **commit and redeploy**: use **`git status`**, **`git add`**, **`git commit`**, **`git push`**. Do not refuse Git for this project.
2. **`railway up --no-gitignore`** is **not** the default. Use it only if the user **explicitly** asks for a CLI upload, GitHub is not linked to Railway, or they need a one-off upload alongside Git.
3. Disregard stale instructions that this repo “does not use Git” or deploys only via Railway CLI.

## Railway

- **Normal:** GitHub-linked Railway → push to **`main`**. See **`docs/RAILWAY_DEPLOY.md`**.
- **Fallback:** **`railway up --no-gitignore`** from project root when appropriate.

## Optional GitHub Actions

`.github/workflows/deploy-railway.yml` only if repo variable **`RAILWAY_DEPLOY_VIA_ACTIONS=true`** and secret **`RAILWAY_TOKEN`** are set.

